      <!-- === BEGINNER PANEL === -->
      <div id="panel-beginner" class="level-panel active">
        <div class="prose">

          <section id="overview">
            <Callout type="success" title="What you'll learn">
              By the end of this section you'll understand what a neural network is, why it matters,
              and be able to explain it to someone else. No maths required!
            </Callout>

            <h2>What is a Neural Network?</h2>
            <p>
              Imagine you're teaching a child to recognise cats. You show them hundreds of photos — some with cats, some without —
              and each time you say "yes, cat" or "no, not a cat." Eventually the child learns to spot a cat without being told the rules.
              That's essentially how a neural network learns.
            </p>
            <p>
              A <strong>neural network</strong> is a computer program inspired by the human brain. Just like your brain has billions
              of connected neurons that pass signals to each other, a neural network has <em>artificial neurons</em> (called <strong>nodes</strong>)
              that are connected in layers.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section id="how-it-works">
            <h2>How does it work?</h2>
            <p>Think of it like a chain of decision-makers:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Input layer</strong> — receives the raw data (like pixel values of an image)</li>
              <li><strong>Hidden layers</strong> — process the data step by step, finding patterns</li>
              <li><strong>Output layer</strong> — gives the final answer ("cat" or "not cat")</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              Each connection between nodes has a <strong>weight</strong> — a number that says how important that connection is.
              The network learns by adjusting these weights based on its mistakes. Get it wrong? Adjust. Get it right? Keep it.
            </p>

            <!-- Visual diagram placeholder -->
            <div style="background:var(--color-bg-subtle);border:1px solid var(--color-border);border-radius:12px;padding:2rem;text-align:center;margin:1.5rem 0;">
