          </section>

          <section id="training">
            <h2>Learning from mistakes</h2>
            <p>
              Here's the magic: the network starts knowing <em>nothing</em>. Every weight starts as a random guess.
              Then it sees thousands of examples, makes predictions, and each time it's wrong, a process called
              <strong>backpropagation</strong> adjusts its weights slightly in the right direction.
              After millions of adjustments, it becomes surprisingly accurate.
            </p>
            <Callout type="info" title="Real-world example">
              Netflix uses neural networks to recommend shows. It's learned that people who like certain movies
              also tend to like others — without ever being told the rules. It figured it out from watching millions of people's viewing habits.
            </Callout>
          </section>

